viewer discretion is advised]

3
00:00:20,100 --> 00:00:21,430
How many cups of coffee did you have?

4
00:00:22,050 --> 00:00:23,350
Do you know any limits?

5
00:00:23,400 --> 00:00:25,130
Just stop being so cute.

6
00:00:27,610 --> 00:00:29,050
Don't ever push through it again, alright?

7
00:00:29,100 --> 00:00:30,100
I'm worried about you.

8
00:00:30,410 --> 00:00:31,730
Did you just take me to your house?

9
00:00:31,780 --> 00:00:32,780
I brought Duang with me today.

10
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:34,300
Answer me.

11
00:00:34,590 --> 00:00:36,520
Will you be my boyfriend, Duang?

12
00:00:38,350 --> 00:00:39,350
Of course, I will.

13
00:00:40,510 --> 00:00:41,970
Through every chapter,

14
00:00:42,560 --> 00:00:44,000
it's always gonna be you, Qin.

15
00:00:44,300 --> 00:00:45,800
It's always gonna be you, Duang.

16
00:00:56,550 --> 00:00:57,990
I love you.

17
00:01:03,490 --> 00:01:04,750
What are you looking at, good boy?

18
00:01:06,710 --> 00:01:07,690
I love you, too.

19
00:01:08,450 --> 00:01:09,250
Hm?

20
00:01:10,730 --> 00:01:12,710
I love you, too.

21
00:01:15,630 --> 00:01:16,950
It's a shame

22
00:01:17,880 --> 00:01:19,800
that I didn't get to meet you
back in high school.

23
00:01:21,490 --> 00:01:22,630
What would you do if you did?

24
00:01:23,750 --> 00:01:26,050
I would've hit on you back then.

25
00:01:26,950 --> 00:01:28,950
If we had started dating back then,

26
00:01:28,990 --> 00:01:30,050
we might have broken up.

27
00:01:30,930 --> 00:01:32,470
Impossible.

28
00:01:33,229 --> 00:01:34,950
I'd never break up with you.

29
00:01:35,550 --> 00:01:37,490
You can't break up on your own either.

30
00:01:38,750 --> 00:01:41,530
No, let's not talk about this.

31
00:01:43,570 --> 00:01:45,650
I thank you for choosing me.

32
00:01:47,970 --> 00:01:50,590
It's because we choose each other, Duang.

33
00:01:53,370 --> 00:01:56,950
From now on,
I'll devote my love to you even more.

34
00:01:59,729 --> 00:02:00,950
Listen.

35
00:02:01,510 --> 00:02:04,390
I'll also love you even more.

36
00:02:10,470 --> 00:02:11,830
I'm starving.

37
00:02:13,350 --> 00:02:14,490
What time is this?

38
00:02:21,990 --> 00:02:22,950
It's 2 A.M.

39
00:02:28,250 --> 00:02:30,610
Making this cute face...

40
00:02:31,290 --> 00:02:32,950
You want stir-fried shrimp with garlic?

41
00:02:35,150 --> 00:02:36,010
You know me too well.

42
00:02:37,850 --> 00:02:38,710
Well...

43
00:02:38,710 --> 00:02:40,650
We'll go to the restaurant
when you're free.

44
00:02:41,190 --> 00:02:42,950
For now, let's have instant noodles.

45
00:02:42,950 --> 00:02:44,329
I'll make them for you.

46
00:02:45,230 --> 00:02:46,490
You're spoiling me again.

47
00:02:47,870 --> 00:02:49,270
Only with you.

48
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:01,000
[Duang With You]

49
00:03:10,970 --> 00:03:15,320
♫I'm not leaving soon, so bear with me♫

50
00:03:15,510 --> 00:03:20,460
♫Wherever you are is where I'll always be♫

51
00:03:20,530 --> 00:03:24,310
♫Wherever you go, I'll find you eventually♫

52
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:26,660
♫You may push me away, but I won't flee♫

53
00:03:26,690 --> 00:03:29,630
♫Who would you love if it weren't me?♫

54
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:31,980
♫So, wanna make a deal, maybe?♫

55
00:03:32,020 --> 00:03:34,320
♫Alright, alright, don't worry♫

56
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:36,670
♫Just date me first, take it easy♫

57
00:03:36,720 --> 00:03:39,050
♫I'll be so cute you'll fall naturally♫

58
00:03:39,110 --> 00:03:41,430
♫No matter what, you'll always run into me♫

59
00:03:41,510 --> 00:03:43,720
♫Okay, okay, let it be♫

60
00:03:43,750 --> 00:03:46,060
♫I know you're also into me,♫

61
00:03:46,110 --> 00:03:48,850
♫Don't you feel the same? I can see♫

62
00:03:49,470 --> 00:03:54,850
♫I'll keep on flirting, don't try to avoid me♫

63
00:03:54,880 --> 00:03:59,870
♫'Cause I won't stop till you fall for me♫

64
00:03:59,900 --> 00:04:04,370
♫I'll keep on flirting, I won't stop, I guarantee♫

65
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:10,740
♫I'll love you hard,
and once you say yes, I'll set you free♫

66
00:04:10,760 --> 00:04:12,040
[Duang With You]

67
00:04:13,210 --> 00:04:14,250
Hurry up,

68
00:04:14,290 --> 00:04:15,930
so I can take a shower.

69
00:04:16,950 --> 00:04:18,950
You can take a shower now.
I'm fine.

70
00:04:19,690 --> 00:04:21,410
You are, but I'm not.

71
00:04:21,670 --> 00:04:22,670
Quickly.

72
00:04:42,040 --> 00:04:43,140
Hurry up,

73
00:04:43,510 --> 00:04:44,950
then you can shower right after me.

74
00:04:46,540 --> 00:04:47,920
You can take your time.

75
00:04:47,950 --> 00:04:49,790
You've got no classes today.

76
00:04:50,250 --> 00:04:52,490
I do, but I can be late.

77
00:04:52,490 --> 00:04:53,770
It's fine.

78
00:04:55,230 --> 00:04:56,470
You can't be late.

79
00:04:56,520 --> 00:04:57,610
I'm coming with you.

80
00:05:00,690 --> 00:05:01,710
Huh?

81
00:05:02,490 --> 00:05:03,670
Why are you surprised?

82
00:05:04,030 --> 00:05:05,530
It's just me hanging out
in class with you.

83
00:05:12,950 --> 00:05:13,810
Ow!

84
00:05:14,110 --> 00:05:15,530
Do you really have to be this excited?

85
00:05:15,750 --> 00:05:17,410
You don't get it.

86
00:05:17,410 --> 00:05:18,750
Are you trying to kill me?

87
00:05:19,590 --> 00:05:21,150
Stop saying that.

88
00:05:21,150 --> 00:05:23,690
If you die, I'll get myself a new lover.

89
00:05:23,970 --> 00:05:24,950
You can't!

90
00:05:24,950 --> 00:05:26,590
I don't want that to happen.

91
00:05:31,570 --> 00:05:32,550
Get out already.

92
00:05:32,550 --> 00:05:33,370
I'm taking a shower.

93
00:05:34,670 --> 00:05:35,630
Okay.

94
00:05:35,630 --> 00:05:36,750
I'll leave now.

95
00:05:36,750 --> 00:05:38,470
I'm not going to die
anytime soon, either.

96
00:05:38,470 --> 00:05:41,310
You can only have me
as your sweetheart, alright?

97
00:05:47,730 --> 00:05:48,950
I know.

98
00:05:49,730 --> 00:05:51,150
You can't be with anyone else either.

99
00:05:56,010 --> 00:05:57,210
Now, get out.

100
00:06:17,020 --> 00:06:19,990
Fit check. Fit check.

101
00:06:21,770 --> 00:06:22,950
Your shirt actually fits.

102
00:06:24,190 --> 00:06:24,950
One second...

103
00:06:31,450 --> 00:06:33,390
I love this fragrance when it's on you.

104
00:06:44,290 --> 00:06:45,270
We're wearing the same one.

105
00:06:47,150 --> 00:06:47,950
Let's take a selfie.

106
00:07:01,150 --> 00:07:02,710
Why do you want to take selfies?

107
00:07:06,350 --> 00:07:06,950
Just take a look.

108
00:07:21,980 --> 00:07:23,240
What's the matter,

109
00:07:23,410 --> 00:07:23,970
huh?

110
00:07:25,350 --> 00:07:26,710
I'm fine.

111
00:07:32,070 --> 00:07:33,130
What's wrong?

112
00:07:34,010 --> 00:07:34,470
Huh?

113
00:07:34,470 --> 00:07:35,730
I can tell something's wrong.

114
00:07:36,090 --> 00:07:36,690
What's wrong?

115
00:07:37,650 --> 00:07:38,710
Don't tease me.

116
00:07:43,230 --> 00:07:44,650
I'm not teasing you.

117
00:07:47,230 --> 00:07:48,950
Why are you turning away from me?

118
00:07:54,530 --> 00:07:55,990
Aww...

119
00:07:57,130 --> 00:07:59,550
It's okay. Don't cry.

120
00:08:01,790 --> 00:08:03,130
Let me get myself ready first,

121
00:08:03,130 --> 00:08:04,170
or you'll be late.

122
00:08:17,440 --> 00:08:20,220
So he finally made it official
on Close Friends?

123
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:22,920
Well, you're like
a caretaker prime minister.

124
00:08:22,950 --> 00:08:25,610
Even though you take the position,
nobody counts it.

125
00:08:29,970 --> 00:08:32,210
You guys are so jealous! You meanie!

126
00:08:33,549 --> 00:08:34,470
Can we go now?

127
00:08:38,190 --> 00:08:39,350
Alright. Let's go.

128
00:08:46,670 --> 00:08:48,510
- Hey!
- Whoa!

129
00:08:48,510 --> 00:08:52,290
What's the tagged selfie
on Instagram about?

130
00:08:52,290 --> 00:08:54,450
"I'm all yours."

131
00:08:54,450 --> 00:08:55,490
Seriously?

132
00:08:55,490 --> 00:08:57,490
Did you steal his phone to post it?

133
00:08:57,690 --> 00:08:59,450
He didn't. I typed it myself.

134
00:08:59,450 --> 00:09:00,330
- Huh?!
- Huh?

135
00:09:03,630 --> 00:09:04,950
Do you want more snacks?

136
00:09:05,410 --> 00:09:07,330
I'll get them
before the professor calls the roll.

137
00:09:09,690 --> 00:09:11,690
Well, shall we head inside?

138
00:09:14,750 --> 00:09:16,030
Can we sit in the back?

139
00:09:16,770 --> 00:09:17,650
Sure thing.

140
00:09:18,010 --> 00:09:20,010
Qin is talking as if
he's going to be in our class.

141
00:09:20,010 --> 00:09:20,710
Yeah.

142
00:09:20,710 --> 00:09:21,330
Mm.

143
00:09:21,330 --> 00:09:22,190
Is the professor strict?

144
00:09:22,390 --> 00:09:22,950
- Huh?!
- Huh?

145
00:09:23,970 --> 00:09:25,630
Why the hell are you guys surprised?

146
00:09:27,310 --> 00:09:29,290
Your shirt looks a bit tight, no?

147
00:09:29,290 --> 00:09:30,390
Switching up your look?

148
00:09:30,390 --> 00:09:30,950
Yeah.

149
00:09:31,810 --> 00:09:32,610
Well...

150
00:09:33,870 --> 00:09:34,950
I'm wearing his shirt.

151
00:09:38,090 --> 00:09:40,950
What's weird about wearing
my boyfriend's clothes?

152
00:09:41,230 --> 00:09:41,990
- Huh?!
- Huh?

153
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:46,000
I

154
00:09:46,330 --> 00:09:47,350
and Qin

155
00:09:47,730 --> 00:09:48,950
are now boyfriends.

156
00:09:49,370 --> 00:09:50,410
What did you say?

157
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:52,920
That made me get up from my seat.

158
00:09:53,170 --> 00:09:53,950
So?

159
00:09:53,950 --> 00:09:54,950
Want me to repeat that?

160
00:09:55,610 --> 00:09:56,610
I

161
00:09:56,610 --> 00:09:57,770
and Qin

162
00:09:58,190 --> 00:09:59,730
are boyfriends now.

163
00:10:02,100 --> 00:10:03,550
Qin...

164
00:10:03,550 --> 00:10:05,410
I'm so sorry.

165
00:10:05,410 --> 00:10:07,650
- What do you mean by that?
- Ow!

166
00:10:07,650 --> 00:10:08,950
I was just kidding.

167
00:10:08,950 --> 00:10:10,510
Congratulations.

168
00:10:11,450 --> 00:10:12,950
Took you forever.

169
00:10:13,430 --> 00:10:15,950
How do single guys sit in class?

170
00:10:15,950 --> 00:10:18,570
Because couples hug
each other's arms while studying.

171
00:10:18,570 --> 00:10:19,970
Hey! Can you be gentle?

172
00:10:24,030 --> 00:10:24,950
Here. Take a sip.

173
00:10:24,950 --> 00:10:25,530
Drink up.

174
00:10:27,130 --> 00:10:28,270
Students,

175
00:10:29,730 --> 00:10:31,890
when drawing a line,

176
00:10:32,130 --> 00:10:34,570
whether it's a curve, a straight line,

177
00:10:34,570 --> 00:10:36,710
or whatever the fuck it is,

178
00:10:36,710 --> 00:10:38,950
how many times have I told you

179
00:10:39,350 --> 00:10:40,530
not to draw it by hand?

180
00:10:40,530 --> 00:10:41,970
Do you still want it?

181
00:10:41,970 --> 00:10:44,550
- One just arrived today.
- Instead, what do we use to draw it?

182
00:10:45,270 --> 00:10:46,610
Feelings,

183
00:10:46,610 --> 00:10:47,970
emotions,

184
00:10:48,770 --> 00:10:50,950
inspirations,

185
00:10:51,370 --> 00:10:53,000
and life experiences.

186
00:10:53,020 --> 00:10:55,330
I do. How much is it?

187
00:10:55,330 --> 00:10:56,610
And what else?

188
00:10:56,610 --> 00:10:57,510
Tears.

189
00:10:57,510 --> 00:11:00,610
- I'll pay immediately.
- The tears you shed during a heartbreak.

190
00:11:01,410 --> 00:11:02,750
Use your feelings.

191
00:11:02,750 --> 00:11:04,210
55,000 baht.

192
00:11:07,450 --> 00:11:09,450
Express it through your lines.

193
00:11:09,450 --> 00:11:11,330
Put your soul into them.

194
00:11:12,290 --> 00:11:12,950
Pour...

195
00:11:15,630 --> 00:11:16,650
Jamie!

196
00:11:18,950 --> 00:11:20,450
Gosh, what is it, Professor?

197
00:11:20,650 --> 00:11:22,270
I was just resting my eyes.

198
00:11:22,270 --> 00:11:24,710
How many years
do you think I've been a professor?

199
00:11:24,710 --> 00:11:27,330
Do you know how many students
have used that excuse?

200
00:11:27,330 --> 00:11:28,610
Oh...

201
00:11:28,950 --> 00:11:30,950
Professor, have you ever heard of this:

202
00:11:31,130 --> 00:11:33,690
"Waking up looking too handsome,
so back to sleep I go"?

203
00:11:34,030 --> 00:11:35,430
Never heard of that.

204
00:11:35,430 --> 00:11:36,950
Sounds like
you pulled it out of your ass.

205
00:11:38,530 --> 00:11:39,550
Right, right.

206
00:11:43,070 --> 00:11:44,120
Who the hell are you?

207
00:11:44,160 --> 00:11:45,590
You don't look familiar. Who are you?

208
00:11:45,670 --> 00:11:46,310
Uh...

209
00:11:46,310 --> 00:11:47,890
You said that

210
00:11:47,890 --> 00:11:50,290
we have to draw with inspiration?

211
00:11:50,290 --> 00:11:52,670
That's why I brought
my source of inspiration to class.

212
00:11:52,670 --> 00:11:55,330
Sheesh!

213
00:11:55,330 --> 00:11:58,550
Yeah.

214
00:11:58,550 --> 00:12:00,410
Students, this is a great example.

215
00:12:00,410 --> 00:12:01,990
- Your inspiration?
- Yes.

216
00:12:02,650 --> 00:12:03,550
I don't mind that.

217
00:12:03,550 --> 00:12:05,790
Just make sure
he doesn't disturb the other students.

218
00:12:06,390 --> 00:12:07,410
Students.

219
00:12:09,470 --> 00:12:12,750
Lines are very important.

220
00:12:13,890 --> 00:12:16,530
Today, we're drawing a still life,

221
00:12:17,170 --> 00:12:18,950
turning an inanimate object
into something lively.

222
00:12:19,450 --> 00:12:21,370
Thus, for straight lines,

223
00:12:21,370 --> 00:12:24,550
use a protractor to draw the angles.

224
00:12:26,030 --> 00:12:27,830
How would that create a straight line?

225
00:12:29,750 --> 00:12:33,670
There, look at the curves and the shadow.

226
00:12:40,250 --> 00:12:41,950
Ow...

227
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:44,590
I'm freaking tired.

228
00:12:44,760 --> 00:12:45,760
Are you coming with me?

229
00:12:45,830 --> 00:12:46,830
Are you free?

230
00:12:48,190 --> 00:12:49,230
You, seriously...

231
00:12:49,230 --> 00:12:52,230
Why did you force Qin
to sit through class with you?

232
00:12:52,510 --> 00:12:54,330
He wasn't having a tough time here.

233
00:12:54,950 --> 00:12:56,330
I chose to come here,

234
00:12:56,330 --> 00:12:57,850
so we could have
stir-fried garlic shrimp sooner.

235
00:13:00,110 --> 00:13:00,950
That's true.

236
00:13:01,150 --> 00:13:02,590
Let's go eat it, shall we?

237
00:13:07,430 --> 00:13:08,950
- Oh, sorry.
- Let's go.

238
00:13:18,950 --> 00:13:20,590
No care for his friends, whatsoever.

239
00:13:23,150 --> 00:13:26,610
I feel like I've been there with him
throughout his love journey.

240
00:13:26,950 --> 00:13:28,950
Since Day 0,

241
00:13:28,950 --> 00:13:30,550
it's been the two of us.

242
00:13:31,710 --> 00:13:32,610
Shall we pull his legs?

243
00:13:33,830 --> 00:13:34,750
Let's go after him.

244
00:13:36,950 --> 00:13:38,950
What's the hurry, buddy?

245
00:13:40,150 --> 00:13:41,950
You're ditching us
now that you've got Qin?

246
00:13:42,670 --> 00:13:44,370
Who are you guys?

247
00:13:44,770 --> 00:13:46,750
I've never met you two.

248
00:13:48,570 --> 00:13:49,750
Fine, Duang.

249
00:13:49,750 --> 00:13:50,710
You asked for this.

250
00:13:52,510 --> 00:13:53,490
- Move, Qin.
- Oh?

251
00:13:53,490 --> 00:13:54,630
- Please move, Qin.
- Oh?!

252
00:13:54,630 --> 00:13:55,990
- Ha!
- Ow!

253
00:13:57,690 --> 00:13:58,990
- Let go!
- Pae, ready?

254
00:13:58,990 --> 00:13:59,990
Don't!

255
00:13:59,990 --> 00:14:01,970
One...

256
00:14:02,370 --> 00:14:04,390
Two...

257
00:14:04,390 --> 00:14:04,730
Three...

258
00:14:04,730 --> 00:14:06,450
I'm taking Qin to get
some stir-fried garlic shrimp!

259
00:14:07,550 --> 00:14:09,610
Would you like me
to peel the shrimp for you, Qin?

260
00:14:11,170 --> 00:14:12,230
So nosy, you guys.

261
00:14:14,690 --> 00:14:17,270
Qin, help me...

262
00:14:17,690 --> 00:14:19,590
Help me, please.

263
00:14:19,950 --> 00:14:20,950
- Gosh!
- Come on!

264
00:14:21,370 --> 00:14:22,730
- Get up by yourself.
- Help yourself.

265
00:14:29,330 --> 00:14:30,470
- Hey!
- Ah!

266
00:14:31,590 --> 00:14:32,270
That's enough.

267
00:14:32,270 --> 00:14:33,730
We're sending you flying this time.

268
00:14:34,690 --> 00:14:35,950
- One...
- Ah!

269
00:14:35,950 --> 00:14:37,770
Two...

270
00:14:39,770 --> 00:14:40,950
Like the wind!

271
00:15:19,810 --> 00:15:21,230
Nothing is by chance.

272
00:15:32,770 --> 00:15:33,950
Come on!

273
00:15:34,270 --> 00:15:36,270
You're holding his hand
a bit too tight, no?

274
00:15:36,490 --> 00:15:38,130
You want to make that clear, don't you?

275
00:15:38,650 --> 00:15:40,750
I'm the first puppy to be the captain.

276
00:15:41,130 --> 00:15:42,530
The world must know this.

277
00:15:43,630 --> 00:15:45,150
I'm so jealous of him.

278
00:15:45,190 --> 00:15:46,070
- Yeah.
- What captain?

279
00:15:46,120 --> 00:15:47,570
I want to tease him again.

280
00:15:53,130 --> 00:15:53,650
Let's.

281
00:15:58,270 --> 00:15:59,270
Here you go.

282
00:15:59,710 --> 00:16:00,950
If you're not full, we can order more.

283
00:16:02,420 --> 00:16:04,940
It's a weekday,
so why are there so many people?

284
00:16:05,990 --> 00:16:06,950
Hello!

285
00:16:06,950 --> 00:16:07,890
- Aha!
- Oh?

286
00:16:08,190 --> 00:16:10,310
Excuse me, plates for 4 people, please!

287
00:16:10,310 --> 00:16:12,470
Right! Coming right up.

288
00:16:12,470 --> 00:16:13,230
How did you get here?

289
00:16:14,950 --> 00:16:17,790
- Here are your plates.
- Thank you.

290
00:16:17,790 --> 00:16:19,130
Not ordering anything else, aren't you?

291
00:16:20,490 --> 00:16:22,430
What the hell?
Go and sit somewhere else!

292
00:16:22,690 --> 00:16:23,990
Shoo! Shoo!

293
00:16:34,670 --> 00:16:36,150
Do you mind if we sit with you, Qin?

294
00:16:36,950 --> 00:16:37,630
Go ahead.

295
00:16:37,870 --> 00:16:39,570
You guys always ruin my moments.

296
00:16:39,570 --> 00:16:40,590
This is my cue, alright?

297
00:16:40,770 --> 00:16:41,410
Gosh.

298
00:16:41,590 --> 00:16:42,770
We don't have that many moments.

299
00:16:42,770 --> 00:16:43,690
You want to have it all by yourself?

300
00:16:43,970 --> 00:16:44,750
Yeah.

301
00:16:45,150 --> 00:16:47,430
You're the biggest whiner
and crybaby here,

302
00:16:47,430 --> 00:16:48,950
you lover boy of Nakhon Pathom.

303
00:16:49,290 --> 00:16:51,730
You approached Qin through me,

304
00:16:51,730 --> 00:16:54,410
but now that you're dating,
you chose to keep me in the dark.

305
00:16:54,770 --> 00:16:57,190
I was about to tell you,
but you've got no classes today.

306
00:16:58,430 --> 00:16:59,950
Duang, you're so lucky

307
00:17:00,170 --> 00:17:01,430
to have Qin as your sweetheart.

308
00:17:02,250 --> 00:17:03,650
Yeah, look at him.

309
00:17:03,970 --> 00:17:05,970
It's almost impossible to win his heart.

310
00:17:06,490 --> 00:17:09,390
You're so lucky that he says yes.

311
00:17:09,390 --> 00:17:10,490
Ahem!

312
00:17:13,250 --> 00:17:16,530
Allow me to speak up
as the lover boy's best friend.

313
00:17:16,750 --> 00:17:17,690
Duang is such a great guy.

314
00:17:19,609 --> 00:17:21,960
Saying no to him is a big mistake.

315
00:17:23,130 --> 00:17:26,430
Qin, you pulled a secret rare.
Do you know why?

316
00:17:26,990 --> 00:17:29,170
He does everything for you,

317
00:17:29,170 --> 00:17:30,950
treating you like a princess.

318
00:17:31,150 --> 00:17:32,450
You're really lucky, Qin.

319
00:17:32,450 --> 00:17:33,950
Duang is the best there is.

320
00:17:34,770 --> 00:17:35,790
I'd like to object.

321
00:17:36,050 --> 00:17:37,950
My friend Qin is the best.

322
00:17:38,450 --> 00:17:40,450
He doesn't even care
about the Communications Faculty King.

323
00:17:40,450 --> 00:17:41,790
Duang simply lucked out.

324
00:17:41,790 --> 00:17:44,950
Yeah, and soon enough,
Qin will become famous

325
00:17:44,950 --> 00:17:46,090
nationwide

326
00:17:46,090 --> 00:17:47,390
and globally.

327
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:55,020
This is luckier than hitting the jackpot.

328
00:17:56,150 --> 00:17:57,100
- True!
- Right?

329
00:17:57,130 --> 00:17:58,570
- Am I right?
- I agreed with that one.

330
00:17:58,570 --> 00:17:59,590
Qin is the best.

331
00:18:01,170 --> 00:18:02,290
- Stupid Duang!
- Stupid Duang!

332
00:18:03,230 --> 00:18:05,610
I'm not going to call you
"unique" anymore!

333
00:18:05,890 --> 00:18:07,350
I'm going to call you "Stupid Duang"!

334
00:18:07,990 --> 00:18:08,610
Yeah.

335
00:18:08,870 --> 00:18:09,630
Stupid Duang!

336
00:18:12,030 --> 00:18:13,030
What the heck?

337
00:18:14,950 --> 00:18:15,730
Alright. Dig in.

338
00:18:15,730 --> 00:18:16,570
Come on.

339
00:18:21,590 --> 00:18:25,350
Surprise!

340
00:18:26,270 --> 00:18:26,950
For what?

341
00:18:27,930 --> 00:18:28,730
Oh...

342
00:18:29,130 --> 00:18:30,250
You're not excited?

343
00:18:30,250 --> 00:18:31,970
Look what's inside.

344
00:19:04,150 --> 00:19:04,950
Why'd you get me this?

345
00:19:05,310 --> 00:19:05,970
It's expensive.

346
00:19:06,950 --> 00:19:07,710
Oh...

347
00:19:10,010 --> 00:19:10,750
Come on.

348
00:19:11,470 --> 00:19:13,210
You're not delighted?

349
00:19:16,610 --> 00:19:17,710
How much did you pay for it?

350
00:19:21,170 --> 00:19:22,330
50,000 baht?!

351
00:19:22,330 --> 00:19:22,950
Plus 5,000.

352
00:19:23,330 --> 00:19:24,770
- Sell it.
- What?

353
00:19:25,290 --> 00:19:26,950
You want it, don't you?

354
00:19:29,790 --> 00:19:30,950
How much money do you have left?

355
00:19:31,630 --> 00:19:33,450
Mm...

356
00:19:33,870 --> 00:19:35,450
- A decent amount.
- How much?

357
00:19:42,170 --> 00:19:43,730
Sell it, or else I'll be mad at you.

358
00:19:43,730 --> 00:19:45,710
No! Listen to me first.

359
00:19:47,690 --> 00:19:49,210
It's true that
it costs an arm and a leg,

360
00:19:49,470 --> 00:19:50,950
but I really want to give it to you.

361
00:19:51,290 --> 00:19:54,150
It's not that I got it for you simply
because you wanted it either.

362
00:19:54,350 --> 00:19:57,470
This film camera represents me.

363
00:19:58,110 --> 00:19:59,970
When you go out to take photos,

364
00:19:59,970 --> 00:20:02,410
if I can't be there with you,

365
00:20:03,370 --> 00:20:05,870
it'll feel like I am.

366
00:20:11,550 --> 00:20:13,410
I appreciate that you care,

367
00:20:15,150 --> 00:20:16,390
but this is too expensive.

368
00:20:18,950 --> 00:20:20,330
It's not.

369
00:20:20,510 --> 00:20:23,530
It's the first gift
for our relationship.

370
00:20:23,870 --> 00:20:24,650
On top of that,

371
00:20:24,650 --> 00:20:27,410
I'm going to get you
a monthiversary gift

372
00:20:27,410 --> 00:20:29,990
on the 16th of every month
to celebrate the day we started dating.

373
00:20:30,190 --> 00:20:30,950
Don't.

374
00:20:32,070 --> 00:20:33,370
Why buy me gifts every month?

375
00:20:34,670 --> 00:20:37,810
55,000 baht is just too expensive.

376
00:20:38,950 --> 00:20:40,950
Oh, it's not.

377
00:20:40,950 --> 00:20:42,470
Your shoes cost even more.

378
00:20:42,470 --> 00:20:43,770
This is nothing.

379
00:20:43,770 --> 00:20:44,510
Duang.

380
00:20:51,310 --> 00:20:52,270
Yes?

381
00:20:54,450 --> 00:20:55,270
I know.

382
00:21:02,650 --> 00:21:03,830
Return it.

383
00:21:05,570 --> 00:21:08,510
It's the first gift
for our relationship, though.

384
00:21:08,510 --> 00:21:10,170
I do want to accept a gift from you,

385
00:21:10,610 --> 00:21:13,170
but I can't if it costs this much.

386
00:21:13,710 --> 00:21:14,730
I'm your boyfriend,

387
00:21:15,170 --> 00:21:16,570
and I want to be a good partner to you.

388
00:21:16,950 --> 00:21:21,330
You want me to accept
a gift that costs you so much?

389
00:21:21,750 --> 00:21:22,750
I just can't.

390
00:21:30,570 --> 00:21:32,950
Contact the camera store
and get a refund.

391
00:21:34,450 --> 00:21:36,250
Or sell it around Siam.

392
00:21:36,730 --> 00:21:37,990
They might buy it from you.

393
00:21:40,950 --> 00:21:41,710
Understand?

394
00:21:44,670 --> 00:21:45,610
I understand.

395
00:22:11,630 --> 00:22:13,770
Does giving him flowers
at the jazz showcase

396
00:22:13,770 --> 00:22:14,950
feel too simple?

397
00:22:14,950 --> 00:22:15,950
What will you give him, then?

398
00:22:15,950 --> 00:22:17,770
A gift basket?

399
00:22:17,970 --> 00:22:18,950
How about balloons?

400
00:22:19,370 --> 00:22:21,590
How about wearing a mascot suit?

401
00:22:21,590 --> 00:22:22,950
That'd be lovely.

402
00:22:22,950 --> 00:22:24,070
If you want to go overboard,

403
00:22:24,070 --> 00:22:27,630
hire a sound truck for the showcase.

404
00:22:27,630 --> 00:22:28,770
A sound truck, my ass!

405
00:22:28,770 --> 00:22:29,870
No need to be sarcastic.

406
00:22:29,870 --> 00:22:31,470
Good on you for knowing
I was being sarcastic.

407
00:22:31,650 --> 00:22:33,630
What about the 55,000-baht film camera?

408
00:22:33,630 --> 00:22:34,730
Why didn't you give it to him?

409
00:22:35,750 --> 00:22:36,390
Huh?

410
00:22:37,210 --> 00:22:38,730
What kind of camera costs that much?

411
00:22:39,130 --> 00:22:40,750
It's a rare model, you know?

412
00:22:41,230 --> 00:22:42,530
Good on you

413
00:22:42,750 --> 00:22:44,110
for being able to afford it.

414
00:22:44,110 --> 00:22:44,950
You're so rich.

415
00:22:45,370 --> 00:22:48,270
If your brother knew about this,
he'd scold you until your next life.

416
00:22:48,950 --> 00:22:49,930
I'm not rich.

417
00:22:49,930 --> 00:22:51,610
I went broke after buying the camera.

418
00:22:51,610 --> 00:22:53,370
When I gave it to him,
he refused to accept it.

419
00:22:53,370 --> 00:22:55,650
He told me to sell it.
That's why I'm carrying it with me.

420
00:22:55,970 --> 00:22:57,750
Damn, he's ruthless.

421
00:22:59,470 --> 00:23:00,610
He did the right thing.

422
00:23:02,950 --> 00:23:04,310
You agree with him?

423
00:23:04,950 --> 00:23:06,970
Why am I in the wrong for doing so much?

424
00:23:07,670 --> 00:23:10,450
You knew that it was too much.

425
00:23:10,950 --> 00:23:12,950
It's fine. You can overdo something.

426
00:23:12,950 --> 00:23:15,910
But if you can't take care of
yourself after buying it,

427
00:23:15,910 --> 00:23:17,170
what good does that make?

428
00:23:17,390 --> 00:23:18,750
Well, I want to give it to him.

429
00:23:19,650 --> 00:23:22,130
I'm not blaming you
for giving him the gift,

430
00:23:22,330 --> 00:23:24,190
but it's the fucking price.

431
00:23:24,190 --> 00:23:25,950
His mom told me to take care of him.

432
00:23:25,950 --> 00:23:27,370
You're talking nonsense at this point.

433
00:23:27,370 --> 00:23:30,050
Is the point here
not letting you take care of Qin?

434
00:23:30,050 --> 00:23:31,430
Why am I not allowed to do this?

435
00:23:31,430 --> 00:23:32,730
You just don't fucking get it.

436
00:23:32,730 --> 00:23:34,270
Yeah, I really don't fucking get you.

437
00:23:34,270 --> 00:23:36,750
Damn it, why are you guys fighting?

438
00:23:37,470 --> 00:23:38,950
I'm not fighting.

439
00:23:39,510 --> 00:23:42,530
Ask yourself
what you've done, Duang.

440
00:23:42,530 --> 00:23:44,810
What kind of fucking camera
is 55,000 baht?

441
00:23:44,950 --> 00:23:46,630
You're biting off
more than you can chew.

442
00:23:46,630 --> 00:23:48,750
No, why are you being mad at him?

443
00:23:48,750 --> 00:23:50,950
I'm not. I'm just warning him.

444
00:23:50,950 --> 00:23:52,230
Stop being so stupid.

445
00:23:58,010 --> 00:24:00,950
You've never been in a relationship;
you don't get it, Jamie!

446
00:24:04,570 --> 00:24:05,390
Duang!

447
00:24:16,250 --> 00:24:17,750
Jamie, wait!

448
00:24:19,750 --> 00:24:20,750
Damn it.

449
00:24:21,290 --> 00:24:22,330
Duang!

450
00:24:22,630 --> 00:24:24,270
Why the hell did you take it out on him?

451
00:24:24,550 --> 00:24:26,750
Don't take out
your frustration on your friend.

452
00:24:26,950 --> 00:24:29,490
Jamie meant well.

453
00:24:29,970 --> 00:24:33,670
Whenever you want something,
he always makes it happen.

454
00:24:34,170 --> 00:24:35,750
But when he warns you out of goodwill,

455
00:24:35,750 --> 00:24:37,330
this is how you treat him?

456
00:24:37,750 --> 00:24:38,690
Fuck.

457
00:24:39,150 --> 00:24:40,770
I'm going to deal with him first.

458
00:25:22,310 --> 00:25:23,530
Qin, can we do another try?

459
00:25:23,530 --> 00:25:24,970
You made a little bit of a mistake.

460
00:25:25,810 --> 00:25:27,130
You seem distracted.

461
00:25:27,130 --> 00:25:27,950
Right.

462
00:25:31,250 --> 00:25:32,960
One more go, okay?

463
00:25:47,270 --> 00:25:48,110
What is it, Jamie?

464
00:25:48,110 --> 00:25:50,710
Qin, I'd like to talk about Duang.

465
00:25:54,770 --> 00:25:55,430
Mm.

466
00:25:55,430 --> 00:25:57,770
Thank you for not accepting
Duang's expensive gift.

467
00:25:57,990 --> 00:25:58,950
Duang's stupid.

468
00:25:59,330 --> 00:26:00,450
He doesn't listen either.

469
00:26:00,730 --> 00:26:01,790
You had a fight with him?

470
00:26:02,130 --> 00:26:03,530
Not exactly.

471
00:26:03,710 --> 00:26:05,170
The more I talked to him,
the more annoyed I became.

472
00:26:05,350 --> 00:26:06,950
That's why I decided to call you instead.

473
00:26:10,490 --> 00:26:14,250
If you're choosing to be with Cheewin,
then go ahead.

474
00:26:14,450 --> 00:26:16,570
I'd rather stay away from

475
00:26:16,570 --> 00:26:17,370
you

476
00:26:17,370 --> 00:26:18,450
and him.

477
00:26:18,750 --> 00:26:19,870
Get out.

478
00:26:19,870 --> 00:26:21,210
What's the deal?

479
00:26:21,490 --> 00:26:22,730
We're all friends here.

480
00:26:22,730 --> 00:26:23,870
Are you nuts?

481
00:26:24,950 --> 00:26:26,170
Don't be mad at him.

482
00:26:26,650 --> 00:26:28,450
I'm not exactly mad at him, Qin.

483
00:26:28,950 --> 00:26:32,370
But he sees treating someone
to expensive stuff as caring.

484
00:26:32,670 --> 00:26:33,970
I think he needs to be changed.

485
00:26:34,590 --> 00:26:36,390
He still hasn't sold the camera.

486
00:26:36,550 --> 00:26:38,550
I think he's probably on his way now.

487
00:26:39,170 --> 00:26:39,950
Mm.

488
00:26:40,550 --> 00:26:41,590
I'll talk to him.

489
00:26:41,910 --> 00:26:42,950
Right, Qin.

490
00:26:46,570 --> 00:26:47,650
Come on!

491
00:26:47,990 --> 00:26:49,690
You're acting like a child here.

492
00:27:00,950 --> 00:27:01,930
Well, then...

493
00:27:01,930 --> 00:27:02,710
Let's take a break for now.

494
00:27:04,270 --> 00:27:05,630
Gosh...

495
00:27:05,630 --> 00:27:06,690
Finally.

496
00:27:07,130 --> 00:27:07,950
I'm starving.

497
00:27:08,950 --> 00:27:10,610
Go have something then, my friend.

498
00:27:11,570 --> 00:27:12,630
We can't go anywhere.

499
00:27:12,950 --> 00:27:13,990
We'll leave after the practice.

500
00:27:33,570 --> 00:27:34,650
Are you tired?

501
00:27:35,210 --> 00:27:35,890
No.

502
00:27:36,470 --> 00:27:37,550
Let's go sell the camera.

503
00:27:40,050 --> 00:27:40,770
Mm.

504
00:27:41,330 --> 00:27:42,270
Let's do that now.

505
00:27:50,150 --> 00:27:51,370
Can you not make that face?

506
00:27:52,410 --> 00:27:53,650
It's like I've done something wrong.

507
00:27:56,750 --> 00:27:57,690
No.

508
00:27:58,950 --> 00:27:59,990
What face am I making?

509
00:28:03,730 --> 00:28:05,690
You can't afford
to sell the camera, can you?

510
00:28:11,850 --> 00:28:13,770
You're not going to tell me
what you're feeling?

511
00:28:16,510 --> 00:28:17,590
Well, yes.

512
00:28:19,550 --> 00:28:21,990
I really don't want
to sell your first gift.

513
00:28:25,430 --> 00:28:26,370
Let it all out.

514
00:28:27,610 --> 00:28:29,370
Everything I did for you...

515
00:28:30,530 --> 00:28:32,950
I want you to know that I love you.

516
00:28:34,430 --> 00:28:36,950
I want to give you
my love as much as I can.

517
00:28:38,590 --> 00:28:39,950
I want you to be happy.

518
00:28:42,290 --> 00:28:43,770
Because you feel sorry for me?

519
00:28:48,750 --> 00:28:50,370
I heard you talking to my mother.

520
00:28:56,090 --> 00:28:57,630
It's true that I feel sorry for you.

521
00:29:00,610 --> 00:29:02,010
But it's because I love you.

522
00:29:02,210 --> 00:29:04,030
I don't want you to feel sorry for me.

523
00:29:18,950 --> 00:29:19,690
Duang.

524
00:29:20,250 --> 00:29:21,650
Can I ask you something?

525
00:29:22,250 --> 00:29:23,370
What is it, Kim?

526
00:29:25,930 --> 00:29:27,850
Can you stay away from Qin for now?

527
00:29:29,310 --> 00:29:30,730
He can't focus during practice.

528
00:29:30,730 --> 00:29:31,870
What do you mean?

529
00:29:32,110 --> 00:29:32,950
I'm doing fine.

530
00:29:34,250 --> 00:29:36,330
You're not aware that
you can't focus, are you?

531
00:29:43,910 --> 00:29:44,950
It's fine.

532
00:29:45,470 --> 00:29:46,710
I'll be patiently waiting.

533
00:29:53,710 --> 00:29:55,430
I won't disturb you guys
during the practice.

534
00:29:57,750 --> 00:29:59,490
This showcase is a serious one.

535
00:30:00,010 --> 00:30:01,510
It affects our grades, too.

536
00:30:02,230 --> 00:30:02,950
Mm.

537
00:30:03,630 --> 00:30:04,570
I understand.

538
00:30:10,110 --> 00:30:10,950
That said...

539
00:30:11,310 --> 00:30:12,350
I'm heading back.

540
00:30:12,710 --> 00:30:13,790
Good luck.

541
00:30:25,650 --> 00:30:26,430
Kim.

542
00:30:28,170 --> 00:30:29,570
Why the hell did you say that to Duang?

543
00:30:29,890 --> 00:30:30,950
Just tell me what's on your mind.

544
00:30:31,950 --> 00:30:32,950
I know that you love each other,

545
00:30:32,950 --> 00:30:34,690
but you have to focus on your part.

546
00:30:35,390 --> 00:30:36,570
I know what I'm doing.

547
00:30:37,150 --> 00:30:39,210
As for the showcase,
you need to talk to me,

548
00:30:39,230 --> 00:30:40,710
not Duang.

549
00:30:40,730 --> 00:30:42,170
He distracts you.

550
00:30:42,170 --> 00:30:43,450
So we have to tell him too, don't we?

551
00:30:45,190 --> 00:30:47,310
But it's me
who has to take the accountability,

552
00:30:47,750 --> 00:30:48,330
not him.

553
00:30:48,510 --> 00:30:50,230
I didn't blame him, did I?

554
00:30:53,670 --> 00:30:55,630
I'm not someone
who doesn't take responsibility.

555
00:30:57,430 --> 00:30:58,370
On top of that,

556
00:30:59,130 --> 00:31:00,330
I'm one of you guys.

557
00:31:04,950 --> 00:31:06,010
Right, right.

558
00:31:06,510 --> 00:31:07,710
I'm sorry.

559
00:31:10,350 --> 00:31:11,370
I'm sorry, too.

560
00:31:15,410 --> 00:31:17,530
Duang and I have some misunderstandings.

561
00:31:18,750 --> 00:31:19,770
I'll sort it out soon.

562
00:31:22,370 --> 00:31:24,450
As for the lack of focus,

563
00:31:25,530 --> 00:31:26,530
it's on me.

564
00:31:27,750 --> 00:31:28,750
Again, I'm sorry.

565
00:31:29,510 --> 00:31:30,950
Let's do one last practice.

566
00:31:30,950 --> 00:31:32,590
Focus on the practice, okay?

567
00:31:33,130 --> 00:31:34,770
Then, get everything sorted out later.

568
00:31:37,330 --> 00:31:38,950
What do you think
after hearing all of that?

569
00:31:39,270 --> 00:31:41,310
Was I being too harsh on my friend?

570
00:31:43,150 --> 00:31:44,950
You really care
about your friend, don't you?

571
00:31:45,310 --> 00:31:47,150
I never knew you had this side.

572
00:31:48,710 --> 00:31:50,470
He's like a brother to me.

573
00:31:50,470 --> 00:31:51,950
It's fun being together with him.

574
00:31:52,530 --> 00:31:54,710
Also, being around him is comfortable.

575
00:31:56,110 --> 00:31:58,470
If you care about him,
go talk to him nicely.

576
00:31:58,750 --> 00:32:00,490
If you want to say sorry, then go ahead.

577
00:32:19,710 --> 00:32:21,230
You suddenly went quiet.

578
00:32:21,690 --> 00:32:22,950
I thought you were doing something.

579
00:32:25,370 --> 00:32:26,550
Can a fashion student like you

580
00:32:26,950 --> 00:32:27,930
do this?

581
00:32:28,270 --> 00:32:28,950
Tell me.

582
00:32:29,870 --> 00:32:33,230
I didn't enroll in the class
when I had the chance.

583
00:32:33,590 --> 00:32:35,290
It looks complicated.

584
00:32:35,970 --> 00:32:37,410
Do you want me to teach you?

585
00:32:37,410 --> 00:32:38,950
I'm a pro at this.

586
00:32:40,510 --> 00:32:41,190
Mm.

587
00:32:51,210 --> 00:32:52,250
First,

588
00:32:52,510 --> 00:32:53,850
make a slip knot.

589
00:32:56,550 --> 00:32:58,330
Don't say that I'm teaching you...

590
00:32:58,330 --> 00:32:59,770
Well, I am.

591
00:33:01,810 --> 00:33:02,550
Huh?

592
00:33:04,410 --> 00:33:05,550
I'm sorry.

593
00:33:05,810 --> 00:33:07,430
I was way too much into roleplaying.

594
00:33:07,430 --> 00:33:08,950
I'm getting serious now.

595
00:33:09,130 --> 00:33:10,010
There.

596
00:33:12,950 --> 00:33:14,690
What are you making exactly?

597
00:33:15,170 --> 00:33:16,770
It's a scarf for my mother.

598
00:33:18,950 --> 00:33:19,770
There.

599
00:33:20,430 --> 00:33:22,470
Rinse and repeat
until you're out of yarn.

600
00:33:23,330 --> 00:33:24,450
Push it through,

601
00:33:24,450 --> 00:33:25,650
loop it over the front,

602
00:33:25,650 --> 00:33:26,770
and pull it back to where it was.

603
00:33:27,170 --> 00:33:28,150
Then pull it out.

604
00:35:13,990 --> 00:35:14,950
Yes?

605
00:35:15,190 --> 00:35:17,450
Gosh, took you forever.

606
00:35:18,950 --> 00:35:20,330
I was cleaning the room.

607
00:35:21,190 --> 00:35:22,410
Thought you'd pretend to fall asleep

608
00:35:22,950 --> 00:35:24,290
and ignore my calls.

609
00:35:26,430 --> 00:35:27,450
Me?

610
00:35:29,130 --> 00:35:30,330
Get on with it already.

611
00:35:34,530 --> 00:35:35,930
I just want to tell you that...

612
00:35:40,390 --> 00:35:41,330
What is it?

613
00:35:42,310 --> 00:35:43,430
Say it, Jamie.

614
00:35:45,990 --> 00:35:46,950
You're going to apologize to me?

615
00:35:53,550 --> 00:35:55,290
You know me too well.

616
00:36:00,690 --> 00:36:01,410
Well...

617
00:36:01,650 --> 00:36:02,950
I'm too good.

618
00:36:06,950 --> 00:36:07,930
Right.

619
00:36:08,950 --> 00:36:09,810
I'm sorry.

620
00:36:10,950 --> 00:36:12,950
I didn't mean to be harsh.

621
00:36:14,330 --> 00:36:15,750
It wasn't my intention.

622
00:36:16,430 --> 00:36:18,950
I actually meant well.

623
00:36:20,490 --> 00:36:21,670
I'm sorry as well

624
00:36:23,530 --> 00:36:24,670
for being mean to you.

625
00:36:26,530 --> 00:36:27,350
Then that clears things up.

626
00:36:28,770 --> 00:36:30,130
Anything you'd like to tell me?

627
00:36:32,330 --> 00:36:33,750
I get what you and Qin meant

628
00:36:34,070 --> 00:36:35,410
as to why you scolded me.

629
00:36:36,730 --> 00:36:39,530
Nice, concise, to the point,

630
00:36:39,530 --> 00:36:40,450
and sharp.

631
00:36:41,130 --> 00:36:42,690
You impressed me, buddy.

632
00:36:43,210 --> 00:36:44,510
Right.

633
00:36:44,510 --> 00:36:45,950
You two have made up, haven't you?

634
00:36:47,750 --> 00:36:48,950
Love you, Pae.

635
00:36:49,350 --> 00:36:51,270
Gosh. That gave me goosebumps.

636
00:36:53,990 --> 00:36:55,510
I love you, too, Warrior.

637
00:36:58,330 --> 00:36:58,950
Right.

638
00:36:59,510 --> 00:37:00,950
Call me if you need anything.

639
00:37:09,830 --> 00:37:10,710
Right.

640
00:37:11,490 --> 00:37:12,730
I'll call you if I do.

641
00:37:13,250 --> 00:37:14,510
Hey, I'll call you as well.

642
00:37:16,450 --> 00:37:17,570
Right.

643
00:38:01,670 --> 00:38:03,970
Wow...

644
00:38:19,430 --> 00:38:21,330
Why do you love wearing shorts?

645
00:38:21,590 --> 00:38:22,670
It makes me feel things.

646
00:38:24,070 --> 00:38:25,570
They're comfortable.

647
00:38:26,950 --> 00:38:27,950
Do you like them?

648
00:38:32,610 --> 00:38:34,950
My legs, do you like them?

649
00:38:36,450 --> 00:38:38,190
Nonsense.

650
00:38:43,490 --> 00:38:45,550
You love kissing my legs in bed.

651
00:38:45,550 --> 00:38:46,950
Do you like mine that much, Jamie?

652
00:38:49,730 --> 00:38:50,570
Stop it.

653
00:38:52,210 --> 00:38:54,950
Teasing you is
a lot more fun than cooking.

654
00:38:57,070 --> 00:38:58,590
Will we get to have dinner or what?

655
00:38:58,590 --> 00:39:00,270
Why do you love tempting me?

656
00:39:01,230 --> 00:39:02,630
I'm not tempting you.

657
00:39:02,950 --> 00:39:04,570
You're the one feeling things.

658
00:39:06,230 --> 00:39:07,990
I'm weak

659
00:39:08,170 --> 00:39:09,630
to beautiful legs,

660
00:39:09,630 --> 00:39:13,990
especially bright ones.
They can make me lose it.

661
00:39:18,310 --> 00:39:20,590
Did I just turn you on?

662
00:39:27,310 --> 00:39:29,350
Oh...

663
00:39:33,730 --> 00:39:34,950
I guess,

664
00:39:35,370 --> 00:39:37,770
I'll get to have you before dinner,

665
00:39:37,770 --> 00:39:38,950
Marvis.

666
00:39:39,350 --> 00:39:40,390
Hm?

667
00:39:56,770 --> 00:39:57,750
No.

668
00:39:57,930 --> 00:39:59,550
I'm not gonna call.
I need to hang tough.

669
00:39:59,550 --> 00:40:00,590
I need to hang tough.

670
00:40:00,590 --> 00:40:01,850
I can do this.

671
00:40:02,130 --> 00:40:03,390
I won't call you.

672
00:40:03,610 --> 00:40:05,410
I won't distract you.

673
00:40:06,310 --> 00:40:07,410
Don't do it.

674
00:40:20,950 --> 00:40:22,430
Hello, where are you?

675
00:40:23,790 --> 00:40:24,530
Uh...

676
00:40:24,530 --> 00:40:26,410
Are you done?
Do you want me to pick you up?

677
00:40:26,770 --> 00:40:27,570
No need.

678
00:40:28,410 --> 00:40:29,690
I'm at your doorstep.

679
00:40:29,930 --> 00:40:30,310
Huh?

680
00:40:31,130 --> 00:40:32,390
At my doorstep?

681
00:40:33,570 --> 00:40:34,270
Mm.

682
00:40:35,450 --> 00:40:36,950
Go inside without me.

683
00:40:37,170 --> 00:40:38,590
I'll send you the password in the chat.

684
00:40:57,990 --> 00:40:58,950
Too cute.

685
00:41:34,330 --> 00:41:35,330
This...

686
00:41:35,910 --> 00:41:37,430
You bought it for 55,000 baht, right?

687
00:41:40,950 --> 00:41:41,970
If you're not going to sell it,

688
00:41:43,170 --> 00:41:45,310
then let it be
the gift we bought together.

689
00:41:46,130 --> 00:41:46,950
How about that?

690
00:41:48,670 --> 00:41:49,730
The gift we bought together?

691
00:41:50,570 --> 00:41:52,730
Let me split the bill.

692
00:41:54,230 --> 00:41:55,230
Hey, but...

693
00:41:55,230 --> 00:41:57,630
I'm accepting
the gift you want to give me.

694
00:41:58,870 --> 00:42:00,270
I simply want to split the bill.

695
00:42:01,570 --> 00:42:03,970
Consider this our film camera.

696
00:42:07,570 --> 00:42:08,290
Can we do that?

697
00:42:10,690 --> 00:42:11,450
Sure.

698
00:42:12,950 --> 00:42:13,850
Yes, we can.

699
00:42:15,390 --> 00:42:16,590
Give me the QR code.

700
00:42:16,700 --> 00:42:17,810
I'm paying you.

701
00:42:24,730 --> 00:42:25,590
Duang?

702
00:42:38,250 --> 00:42:39,550
A gift...

703
00:42:40,950 --> 00:42:42,730
It should simply be anything

704
00:42:42,950 --> 00:42:44,670
that you want to give.

705
00:42:46,070 --> 00:42:49,190
It doesn't have to be expensive.

706
00:42:49,730 --> 00:42:52,370
No need to make up for my family, too.

707
00:42:54,430 --> 00:42:56,950
Remember the first few days
you were trying to win my heart?

708
00:42:59,670 --> 00:43:01,770
You made me a box of chocolates.

709
00:43:02,770 --> 00:43:05,570
Do you still remember
what kind of emotion was behind that gift?

710
00:43:06,570 --> 00:43:07,950
I gave it because I wanted to.

711
00:43:08,310 --> 00:43:09,350
That's simply enough.

712
00:43:09,830 --> 00:43:12,670
That already has a charm
to delight the receiver.

713
00:43:14,950 --> 00:43:15,970
I get it now.

714
00:43:16,530 --> 00:43:20,610
I'll capture a whole bunch
of our memories with this film camera!

715
00:43:20,610 --> 00:43:21,410
Mm.

716
00:43:23,410 --> 00:43:24,110
By the way,

717
00:43:24,530 --> 00:43:25,590
give me your LINE ID.

718
00:43:29,490 --> 00:43:32,210
It'd be weird
not to exchange IDs as a couple, right?

719
00:43:32,710 --> 00:43:34,230
Here's your boyfriend's LINE ID.

720
00:43:40,530 --> 00:43:41,530
Added.

721
00:43:44,730 --> 00:43:45,570
Oh.

722
00:43:46,390 --> 00:43:48,570
How did you know I'm staying here?

723
00:43:48,870 --> 00:43:50,270
How did you know where my place is?

724
00:43:51,310 --> 00:43:52,530
Well...

725
00:43:54,230 --> 00:43:55,310
Hello, Jamie.

726
00:43:55,310 --> 00:43:56,090
Are you with Duang?

727
00:43:56,470 --> 00:43:58,330
I'm not with him, Qin.

728
00:43:58,550 --> 00:44:00,290
How about looking for him at his place?

729
00:44:04,250 --> 00:44:05,270
I'm hungry.

730
00:44:05,270 --> 00:44:06,450
I got us boiled chicken and rice.

731
00:44:06,950 --> 00:44:09,570
Let me get it plated for us.

732
00:44:11,410 --> 00:44:13,930
I'm really happy
that you came to my place.

733
00:44:14,950 --> 00:44:16,650
My room without you is just...

734
00:44:16,920 --> 00:44:17,970
It feels weird.

735
00:44:23,510 --> 00:44:24,290
Why?

736
00:44:26,030 --> 00:44:27,390
So you're hooked on me now?

737
00:44:28,950 --> 00:44:29,510
Mm.

738
00:44:31,990 --> 00:44:33,350
Qin?!

739
00:44:34,950 --> 00:44:36,350
You didn't answer my calls.

740
00:44:36,520 --> 00:44:37,770
You didn't call me back either.

741
00:44:38,950 --> 00:44:40,750
- You called me?
- Take a look.

742
00:44:42,610 --> 00:44:43,430
What?!

743
00:44:43,830 --> 00:44:45,190
You did call me!

744
00:44:45,190 --> 00:44:47,250
You must have called me
when I was getting changed.

745
00:44:47,450 --> 00:44:50,250
I was going to text you when I got here,

746
00:44:50,250 --> 00:44:52,390
but I worried I'd distract you.

747
00:44:52,390 --> 00:44:53,530
Kim said...

748
00:44:53,830 --> 00:44:56,130
The jazz showcase is

749
00:44:56,130 --> 00:44:59,130
very important to you guys.

750
00:45:00,290 --> 00:45:03,190
It was my fault for not being able
to concentrate during practice.

751
00:45:04,190 --> 00:45:05,710
I was worried about my boyfriend.

752
00:45:12,510 --> 00:45:14,190
I didn't think much of it.

753
00:45:15,550 --> 00:45:16,690
Liar.

754
00:45:19,170 --> 00:45:20,770
Well, I kind of did.

755
00:45:23,150 --> 00:45:24,950
I really love you,

756
00:45:25,350 --> 00:45:26,950
and I don't want to cause you problems.

757
00:45:30,210 --> 00:45:32,450
You aren't the only one in love here.

758
00:45:32,450 --> 00:45:33,890
I love you, too.

759
00:45:37,250 --> 00:45:38,290
Also...

760
00:45:38,290 --> 00:45:39,710
Can you not
just disappear without warning?

761
00:45:39,710 --> 00:45:40,570
I'm not used to it,

762
00:45:40,950 --> 00:45:42,770
not seeing new messages

763
00:45:43,130 --> 00:45:44,730
from you on Instagram.

764
00:45:48,450 --> 00:45:49,390
Sure thing.

765
00:45:50,270 --> 00:45:52,050
I won't simply disappear.

766
00:45:53,510 --> 00:45:54,730
You now know that

767
00:45:55,610 --> 00:45:57,290
I love only you, right?

768
00:45:57,770 --> 00:46:00,170
I love you very much.

769
00:46:01,210 --> 00:46:01,970
I do.

770
00:46:02,330 --> 00:46:04,370
Even the password...

771
00:46:04,950 --> 00:46:05,650
Oops.

772
00:46:06,310 --> 00:46:07,830
It's my birth date.

773
00:46:10,770 --> 00:46:13,310
When I knew what your birth date was,

774
00:46:13,310 --> 00:46:15,450
I got excited and set it as the password.

775
00:46:18,630 --> 00:46:19,790
When are you going to dig in?

776
00:46:19,970 --> 00:46:20,950
I'm hungry now.

777
00:46:21,490 --> 00:46:22,670
Let's.

778
00:46:26,290 --> 00:46:27,290
You have no clue

779
00:46:27,630 --> 00:46:29,350
how many things about you I've looked up,

780
00:46:29,630 --> 00:46:31,470
like what you like and dislike.

781
00:46:33,210 --> 00:46:34,690
Why wouldn't I know?

782
00:46:37,150 --> 00:46:39,190
I scolded you for it.
Can't you remember?

783
00:46:45,830 --> 00:46:46,950
What the fuck are you looking at?

784
00:46:47,530 --> 00:46:48,950
Yeah, you're right.

785
00:46:49,870 --> 00:46:51,610
This time, it comes with your voice.

786
00:46:51,610 --> 00:46:52,530
You want more?

787
00:46:53,470 --> 00:46:54,950
I can let you scold me all day.

788
00:46:55,230 --> 00:46:56,670
What the fuck are you looking at?

789
00:46:57,490 --> 00:46:58,650
Any snacks in the fridge?

790
00:46:59,470 --> 00:47:00,950
I don't think so, but I'll check it.

791
00:47:00,950 --> 00:47:02,370
No, I'll do it.

792
00:47:10,110 --> 00:47:11,270
There are cans of beer. Want one?

793
00:47:12,170 --> 00:47:12,950
I do.

794
00:47:17,750 --> 00:47:18,950
I'm drinking it outdoors.

795
00:47:19,530 --> 00:47:20,490
It hits better.

796
00:47:21,250 --> 00:47:22,490
Follow me when you're done.

797
00:47:48,150 --> 00:47:49,470
Better watch it, though.

798
00:47:49,890 --> 00:47:52,470
I'll devour you
the minute you get drunk.

799
00:47:57,630 --> 00:47:59,150
You're the one who needs to watch it.

800
00:48:01,640 --> 00:48:02,700
What do you mean?

801
00:48:03,650 --> 00:48:05,190
You're going to devour me?

802
00:48:05,550 --> 00:48:06,610
Aww...

803
00:48:06,610 --> 00:48:07,810
I'll allow it.

804
00:48:10,670 --> 00:48:11,730
Ridiculous.

805
00:48:32,010 --> 00:48:33,230
It reminds me of you,

806
00:48:33,230 --> 00:48:34,730
so I got it for you.

807
00:48:35,190 --> 00:48:36,470
Aww...

808
00:48:36,470 --> 00:48:37,910
It's so sweet.

809
00:48:37,910 --> 00:48:38,950
Thank you.

810
00:48:39,230 --> 00:48:41,210
My heart's pounding right now.

811
00:48:42,950 --> 00:48:45,330
This already makes me happy.

812
00:48:48,050 --> 00:48:48,950
By the way...

813
00:48:49,430 --> 00:48:51,150
Why does this doggo remind you of me?

814
00:48:52,250 --> 00:48:53,130
Well...

815
00:48:54,330 --> 00:48:55,950
You're always my protector.

816
00:48:57,070 --> 00:49:00,810
So I want this little guy
to protect you on my behalf.

817
00:49:04,470 --> 00:49:07,750
I thought you'd say I looked like a dog.

818
00:49:15,510 --> 00:49:16,570
Whose guitar is that?

819
00:49:18,330 --> 00:49:19,830
It's Funan's.

820
00:49:19,830 --> 00:49:21,370
I can't play it, actually.

821
00:49:21,370 --> 00:49:22,570
I can't play any instruments.

822
00:49:22,570 --> 00:49:24,250
But you can play
all sorts of instruments, no?

823
00:49:27,470 --> 00:49:28,950
Whoa...

824
00:49:29,530 --> 00:49:32,010
You already look very cool posing!

825
00:49:32,950 --> 00:49:35,590
Can I make you some noise?

826
00:49:35,590 --> 00:49:36,670
Stop playing around already.

827
00:49:43,270 --> 00:49:48,190
♫Some day, I might walk through time,♫

828
00:49:48,190 --> 00:49:53,130
♫Where our ticking clocks are aligned♫

829
00:49:53,130 --> 00:49:58,330
♫And when time brings us together,♫

830
00:49:58,330 --> 00:50:03,150
♫I'll hold you forever,♫

831
00:50:03,670 --> 00:50:06,650
♫The one I've been waiting for♫

832
00:50:13,330 --> 00:50:13,810
Right.

833
00:50:14,570 --> 00:50:16,270
When I was at your house,

834
00:50:16,750 --> 00:50:18,730
I saw a massive piano.

835
00:50:19,170 --> 00:50:20,390
Other instruments you can play?

836
00:50:21,190 --> 00:50:22,490
Can you play the violin?

837
00:50:23,130 --> 00:50:24,390
Kind of.

838
00:50:25,510 --> 00:50:28,310
"Kind of" means
you're a pro at it, I'm sure.

839
00:50:28,570 --> 00:50:30,950
Even your mom says that you're talented.

840
00:50:31,210 --> 00:50:31,770
Mm...

841
00:50:31,770 --> 00:50:33,350
That reminds me.

842
00:50:33,350 --> 00:50:35,690
I tried to be as polite as I could,

843
00:50:36,290 --> 00:50:37,950
but I was too chatty, right?

844
00:50:40,290 --> 00:50:41,230
Fortunately,

845
00:50:41,230 --> 00:50:43,710
at least we became
boyfriends at your house,

846
00:50:48,770 --> 00:50:51,210
creating new memories there
on top of that.

847
00:51:04,190 --> 00:51:05,510
Did I say something wrong?

848
00:51:38,010 --> 00:51:39,910
This is my bedroom.

849
00:51:59,130 --> 00:52:00,570
Actually,

850
00:52:02,050 --> 00:52:04,090
I've never told anyone about this.

851
00:52:07,410 --> 00:52:09,430
But I want to tell you now.

852
00:52:17,890 --> 00:52:19,650
I'm always quiet,

853
00:52:21,530 --> 00:52:24,270
and I refuse to talk
to anyone I'm not close to.

854
00:52:28,170 --> 00:52:29,730
There's a reason behind it.

855
00:52:30,950 --> 00:52:31,870
I get it.

856
00:52:32,950 --> 00:52:35,430
You're an introvert. I know that.

857
00:52:36,190 --> 00:52:37,770
No need to hide it.

858
00:52:38,950 --> 00:52:40,570
You heard it from my mother, didn't you?

859
00:52:53,990 --> 00:52:56,290
I was just an ordinary child.

860
00:52:59,750 --> 00:53:01,350
I talked like others.

861
00:53:04,470 --> 00:53:05,830
I was just as curious

862
00:53:06,370 --> 00:53:07,730
as other kids.

863
00:53:09,690 --> 00:53:11,410
The only person I could ask anything of

864
00:53:12,130 --> 00:53:13,330
was my babysitter.

865
00:53:14,490 --> 00:53:16,750
My parents weren't there for me.

866
00:53:19,590 --> 00:53:21,750
What is this called?

867
00:53:24,090 --> 00:53:25,130
An elephant.

868
00:53:26,290 --> 00:53:27,270
Don't know what it is?

869
00:53:29,870 --> 00:53:31,250
What about this one in Thai?

870
00:53:32,550 --> 00:53:33,630
"Ma."

871
00:53:34,950 --> 00:53:36,030
Are you stupid?

872
00:53:36,290 --> 00:53:37,690
You don't know what a horse in Thai is?

873
00:53:39,350 --> 00:53:41,930
- Why does it sound like "mama"?
- Gosh!

874
00:53:45,660 --> 00:53:46,950
Can you just shut up?

875
00:53:47,610 --> 00:53:49,550
Stop asking me questions! So annoying!

876
00:53:49,550 --> 00:53:50,950
- But...
- Gosh!!

877
00:53:54,510 --> 00:53:55,510
Are you crying?

878
00:53:56,950 --> 00:53:57,790
Why are you crying?!

879
00:53:57,790 --> 00:53:58,950
Why the hell are you crying?!

880
00:54:00,510 --> 00:54:01,630
Gosh!

881
00:54:01,990 --> 00:54:03,370
So annoying!

882
00:54:03,910 --> 00:54:05,210
Stop crying already!

883
00:54:06,950 --> 00:54:08,670
I told you to fucking stop crying!

884
00:54:09,850 --> 00:54:10,950
You're not going to stop?

885
00:54:10,950 --> 00:54:12,630
If you keep crying,

886
00:54:12,630 --> 00:54:14,670
I'll throw you out of the house
so that you can cry all day.

887
00:54:14,950 --> 00:54:16,690
Stop it already!

888
00:54:34,370 --> 00:54:35,330
You want to cry, right?!

889
00:54:35,330 --> 00:54:36,950
Then go ahead!

890
00:54:38,410 --> 00:54:40,230
Cry all you want!

891
00:54:40,670 --> 00:54:42,490
Cry here, outside the house.

892
00:54:43,170 --> 00:54:44,950
Are you going to stop?!

893
00:54:45,830 --> 00:54:47,590
You're not going to stop?

894
00:54:47,590 --> 00:54:48,350
Fine!

895
00:54:53,210 --> 00:54:56,510
Papa, mama...

896
00:55:01,950 --> 00:55:03,330
Are you going to stop?

897
00:55:03,610 --> 00:55:04,950
Are you going to shut up?!

898
00:55:05,970 --> 00:55:08,330
If you won't stop,
I'll shove mud inside your mouth.

899
00:55:08,510 --> 00:55:09,490
Are you going to stop?!

900
00:55:40,950 --> 00:55:42,330
Qin.

901
00:55:42,330 --> 00:55:44,210
I have to go to dinner outside tonight.

902
00:55:44,210 --> 00:55:45,830
Would you like to come with me?

903
00:55:47,310 --> 00:55:48,190
No?

904
00:55:48,190 --> 00:55:50,110
You want to stay here
and play all by yourself?

905
00:55:51,850 --> 00:55:53,950
Well then, stay inside with Sorn, okay?

906
00:55:58,530 --> 00:56:00,550
Please take care of Qin, Sorn.

907
00:56:00,950 --> 00:56:01,610
What a relief.

908
00:56:01,610 --> 00:56:04,530
Since having you here,
I've been feeling a lot more comfortable.

909
00:56:04,530 --> 00:56:06,410
Stay with us for years to come, okay?

910
00:56:06,410 --> 00:56:07,230
Yes.

911
00:56:07,230 --> 00:56:08,810
Don't worry.

912
00:56:08,810 --> 00:56:10,570
I'll take good care of Qin.

913
00:56:11,130 --> 00:56:12,190
I'll leave him to you.

914
00:56:12,190 --> 00:56:12,950
Understood.

915
00:56:13,270 --> 00:56:14,250
I'll be going now.

916
00:56:26,270 --> 00:56:27,630
Say anything,

917
00:56:29,170 --> 00:56:30,630
and I'll make you eat mud.

918
00:56:32,950 --> 00:56:33,970
I couldn't do anything.

919
00:56:34,710 --> 00:56:35,930
I wanted to ask for help,

920
00:56:37,430 --> 00:56:39,710
and every time I called for my parents,

921
00:56:40,710 --> 00:56:41,950
they were never there.

922
00:56:42,670 --> 00:56:44,950
They had no idea who I really was

923
00:56:45,130 --> 00:56:45,970
or what I'd been through.

924
00:56:47,550 --> 00:56:49,810
They knew that I wasn't normal.

925
00:56:51,850 --> 00:56:53,850
They took me to a psychiatrist.

926
00:56:54,570 --> 00:56:55,390
Qin.

927
00:56:55,790 --> 00:56:56,950
Did you say hello to him?

928
00:57:00,150 --> 00:57:01,210
Hello.

929
00:57:01,770 --> 00:57:03,330
My name is Kao.

930
00:57:03,570 --> 00:57:04,630
What's your name?

931
00:57:08,950 --> 00:57:09,810
So...

932
00:57:09,810 --> 00:57:13,450
He rarely talks to anyone but his parents.

933
00:57:13,450 --> 00:57:14,530
He's a quiet boy.

934
00:57:14,530 --> 00:57:15,730
He's not sociable.

935
00:57:17,770 --> 00:57:20,950
If that's the case,
can I ask you a question?

936
00:57:24,770 --> 00:57:26,570
Is there anything you'd like to tell me?

937
00:57:34,750 --> 00:57:35,970
If that's the case...

938
00:57:36,950 --> 00:57:39,610
Can I examine
the area under your clothes?

939
00:57:42,250 --> 00:57:43,350
Under his clothes?

940
00:57:43,570 --> 00:57:44,350
Yes.

941
00:57:48,290 --> 00:57:49,190
Qin...

942
00:57:49,630 --> 00:57:50,950
May I take a look, son?

943
00:57:57,770 --> 00:57:58,590
Honey...

944
00:57:58,590 --> 00:58:00,290
Oh? What's this?

945
00:58:01,310 --> 00:58:02,210
Qin?

946
00:58:02,210 --> 00:58:02,950
Oh...

947
00:58:03,450 --> 00:58:04,730
What happened to you?

948
00:58:06,330 --> 00:58:06,950
Honey...

949
00:58:07,390 --> 00:58:08,350
Check the security cameras.

950
00:58:26,430 --> 00:58:27,550
Oh, dear...

951
00:58:27,730 --> 00:58:28,950
Look at this...

952
00:58:32,310 --> 00:58:34,230
You want to cry, right?!

953
00:58:34,350 --> 00:58:35,820
Cry all you want!

954
00:58:36,950 --> 00:58:38,070
Go ahead!

955
00:58:38,070 --> 00:58:38,950
Cry here, outside the house.

956
00:58:42,150 --> 00:58:43,550
Coming home already?

957
00:58:44,510 --> 00:58:45,370
Qin.

958
00:58:45,370 --> 00:58:47,450
Go and wait for me upstairs, okay?

959
00:59:04,310 --> 00:59:05,630
What does this mean?

960
00:59:05,990 --> 00:59:08,150
But there shouldn't be
any cameras there...

961
00:59:08,150 --> 00:59:09,790
Why did you do that?!

962
00:59:10,310 --> 00:59:11,730
I... I didn't mean to.

963
00:59:12,490 --> 00:59:13,710
Pack up your belongings

964
00:59:14,310 --> 00:59:15,730
and get out of my house.

965
00:59:15,730 --> 00:59:18,350
I'm sorry. I'm really sorry.

966
00:59:18,950 --> 00:59:20,170
I'm so sorry.

967
00:59:20,170 --> 00:59:21,710
I didn't mean to do it.

968
00:59:21,890 --> 00:59:22,950
Go and get your stuff

969
00:59:24,030 --> 00:59:25,510
before I call the police.

970
00:59:28,510 --> 00:59:29,870
He's an insufferable brat.

971
00:59:29,870 --> 00:59:32,610
He never listens to what I say.
What the hell was I supposed to do?

972
00:59:33,190 --> 00:59:34,630
If you cared that much about him,

973
00:59:35,370 --> 00:59:36,750
then take care of him yourselves!

974
00:59:37,950 --> 00:59:38,950
Do you want to know something?

975
00:59:40,090 --> 00:59:42,390
Even a dog knows
how to be grateful when you feed it,

976
00:59:42,770 --> 00:59:43,870
unlike you.

977
00:59:43,870 --> 00:59:44,950
Want to know something?

978
00:59:46,030 --> 00:59:48,170
Even a dog loves its pups,

979
00:59:48,530 --> 00:59:49,810
unlike you two.

980
00:59:51,650 --> 00:59:53,550
Hiring you to take care of our son

981
00:59:53,550 --> 00:59:55,190
doesn't mean that we don't love him.

982
00:59:55,190 --> 00:59:57,790
We make a living

983
00:59:57,790 --> 00:59:59,470
to pay for his tuition.

984
00:59:59,870 --> 01:00:02,310
When he grows up, I'm going to teach him

985
01:00:02,310 --> 01:00:04,030
how to be grateful to others,

986
01:00:04,330 --> 01:00:05,330
the quality you lack.

987
01:00:05,330 --> 01:00:07,130
Your parents
must not have taught you what it is.

988
01:00:07,130 --> 01:00:08,490
Don't fucking preach to me!

989
01:00:09,450 --> 01:00:11,670
I hope you have time
to fucking teach him.

990
01:00:12,170 --> 01:00:14,670
You have money,
social status, and everything,

991
01:00:15,130 --> 01:00:16,590
yet you can't spare
the time for your son.

992
01:00:16,590 --> 01:00:18,730
He must've really loved you guys!

993
01:00:19,270 --> 01:00:20,570
Keep treating him like this,

994
01:00:20,950 --> 01:00:23,390
and your son
will end up a problematic child.

995
01:00:23,390 --> 01:00:25,350
Education is important.

996
01:00:25,350 --> 01:00:26,230
Good!

997
01:00:26,630 --> 01:00:28,950
Good. Have him study hard

998
01:00:29,210 --> 01:00:31,390
so that he'll get to meet other people.

999
01:00:31,950 --> 01:00:33,410
After classes,

1000
01:00:33,890 --> 01:00:36,310
he'll get to meet friends
who have good parents.

1001
01:00:36,310 --> 01:00:38,950
Parents who wait
at school to take them home.

1002
01:00:39,210 --> 01:00:41,250
He'll be the only one

1003
01:00:41,250 --> 01:00:43,830
who gets taken care of and driven around
by a babysitter and driver.

1004
01:00:44,010 --> 01:00:44,950
Oh?!

1005
01:00:45,670 --> 01:00:46,550
Here's the kicker.

1006
01:00:46,550 --> 01:00:48,430
He won't get to meet his parents
when he gets home!

1007
01:00:48,430 --> 01:00:50,430
Gosh, what a happy family!

1008
01:00:50,430 --> 01:00:51,950
It's as if he were an orphan!

1009
01:00:52,610 --> 01:00:53,910
I'm curious.

1010
01:00:54,450 --> 01:00:55,530
What will he be like when he grows up?

1011
01:00:55,530 --> 01:00:56,630
Are you done babbling?

1012
01:00:58,130 --> 01:00:59,350
If you are, then get out.

1013
01:00:59,350 --> 01:01:01,150
No need to tell me!

1014
01:01:01,410 --> 01:01:03,830
I'm leaving for sure!

1015
01:01:03,830 --> 01:01:06,630
I'm saying these
because I want your son to hear it, too!

1016
01:01:06,630 --> 01:01:09,230
Even when I'm gone,

1017
01:01:09,230 --> 01:01:11,310
you won't get to be
with your damn parents!

1018
01:01:11,310 --> 01:01:12,370
That's enough.

1019
01:01:12,370 --> 01:01:12,950
Let's leave.

1020
01:01:12,950 --> 01:01:14,510
Where are you going, Miss?

1021
01:01:14,510 --> 01:01:15,710
I'm not done here.

1022
01:01:15,710 --> 01:01:17,550
You can't stand these words already?

1023
01:01:17,550 --> 01:01:19,290
I told you to get out of my house.

1024
01:01:19,690 --> 01:01:21,390
- Get out!
- What I wanted was

1025
01:01:21,970 --> 01:01:23,950
a hug from my parents.

1026
01:01:25,130 --> 01:01:26,150
I wanted them to be with me,

1027
01:01:26,470 --> 01:01:29,530
to give me warmth, like a family would.

1028
01:01:32,300 --> 01:01:33,730
I never got any of that.

1029
01:01:36,190 --> 01:01:37,950
They fired the babysitter,

1030
01:01:39,730 --> 01:01:41,750
and pretended like nothing ever happened.

1031
01:01:48,490 --> 01:01:50,150
They never once hugged me.

1032
01:02:05,310 --> 01:02:06,630
How about this?

1033
01:02:09,960 --> 01:02:12,180
I don't know if it'd work for you,

1034
01:02:13,000 --> 01:02:15,000
but if your past memories

1035
01:02:15,630 --> 01:02:16,950
hurt you,

1036
01:02:22,430 --> 01:02:24,470
it's time to let go
of your younger self's hands

1037
01:02:34,950 --> 01:02:36,470
and hold mine.

1038
01:02:38,550 --> 01:02:39,990
I'll take it from here.

1039
01:03:04,150 --> 01:03:06,510
I was just an ordinary child.

1040
01:03:07,250 --> 01:03:08,950
I talked like others.

1041
01:03:10,070 --> 01:03:11,950
What I wanted was

1042
01:03:14,150 --> 01:03:16,350
a hug from my parents.

1043
01:03:18,690 --> 01:03:20,730
Why the hell are you crying?!

1044
01:03:20,950 --> 01:03:23,210
I only want the best for him.

1045
01:03:23,950 --> 01:03:25,290
Stop crying already!

1046
01:03:27,150 --> 01:03:28,430
That hurt like hell back then, you know?

1047
01:03:28,430 --> 01:03:30,270
You can now explain how you feel?

1048
01:03:30,270 --> 01:03:32,510
- I wish to cry like others, but couldn't.
- Try crying one more time.

1049
01:03:32,510 --> 01:03:34,730
Gosh, what a happy family!

1050
01:03:34,730 --> 01:03:35,890
It's as if he were an orphan!

1051
01:03:35,890 --> 01:03:39,450
- He rarely talks to anyone but his parents.
- You said nothing back then.

1052
01:03:39,450 --> 01:03:42,750
- Mama, papa...
- I told you to shut up!

1053
01:03:42,750 --> 01:03:44,430
I thought...

1054
01:03:44,430 --> 01:03:47,130
Qin wouldn't probably
remember those things.

1055
01:03:47,130 --> 01:03:49,310
It's time to let go
of your younger self's hands.

1056
01:03:49,310 --> 01:03:50,590
Why are you crying?!

1057
01:03:50,590 --> 01:03:53,670
Best of luck
with everything moving forward.

1058
01:04:07,730 --> 01:04:09,190
I promise you...

1059
01:04:12,010 --> 01:04:13,970
I'll always be right by your side.

1060
01:04:19,390 --> 01:04:21,590
I'll be everything for you.

1061
01:04:27,450 --> 01:04:29,150
Walk with me, Qin.

1062
01:05:03,530 --> 01:05:05,290
Don't cry, okay.

1063
01:06:04,850 --> 01:06:06,100
Mom and Dad love you;

1064
01:06:06,700 --> 01:06:08,300
otherwise, they
wouldn't have come back so quickly.

1065
01:06:08,560 --> 01:06:12,040
You said you wanted us to be with you.

1066
01:06:12,160 --> 01:06:13,410
Is everything okay?

1067
01:06:13,690 --> 01:06:14,940
Thank you, Duang,

1068
01:06:15,640 --> 01:06:17,160
for always sticking by my side.

1069
01:06:17,950 --> 01:06:19,770
Do you think people outside will know

1070
01:06:20,400 --> 01:06:22,130
I'm teasing you?

1071
01:06:22,520 --> 01:06:23,990
I want to invite you over for a meal.

1072
01:06:24,360 --> 01:06:27,660
- I'm back!!
- Calm down.

1073
01:06:27,820 --> 01:06:28,830
This is my boyfriend.

1074
01:06:29,030 --> 01:06:30,210
He is...

1075
01:06:31,080 --> 01:06:32,330
Taking a shower together

1076
01:06:33,060 --> 01:06:34,310
helps save the environment.

1077
01:06:34,970 --> 01:06:39,180
♫Have no fear, I'm by your side♫

1078
01:06:39,330 --> 01:06:43,410
♫Let me be the one loving you♫

1079
01:06:43,450 --> 01:06:47,950
♫My heart aches for you
through and through♫

1080
01:06:51,170 --> 01:06:55,370
♫From now on,
my words of love end with you♫

1081
01:06:55,410 --> 01:06:59,450
♫I'm prepared to love you with all my soul♫

1082
01:06:59,490 --> 01:07:03,410
♫My being will be yours as a whole♫

1083
01:07:03,450 --> 01:07:06,690
♫Whatever tomorrow lies,♫

1084
01:07:07,010 --> 01:07:10,890
♫Have no fear, I'm by your side♫

1085
01:07:11,370 --> 01:07:15,450
♫Let me be the one loving you♫

1086
01:07:15,490 --> 01:07:19,570
♫My heart aches for you
through and through♫

1087
01:07:23,210 --> 01:07:29,610
♫From now on,
my words of love only end with you♫

1088
01:07:31,360 --> 01:07:34,540
[Duang With You]

